==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Low-pressure
<hw>Low"-pres`sure</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having, employing, or exerting, a low degree of pressure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>easygoing</er>, 4; <as>as, a
<ex>low-pressure</ex> salesman</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> easygoing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Low-pressure steam engine</b></col>, <cd>a steam engine
in which low steam is used; often applied to a condensing engine even
when steam at high pressure is used. See <er>Steam
engine</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>low-priced</ent>⟦br⟧
